definition.value: Secondary polycythemia is an elevated absolute red blood cell mass caused by enhanced stimulation of red blood cell production by an otherwise normal erythroid lineage that may be congenital or acquired (congenital secondary polycythemia and acquired secondary polycythemia; see these terms).

label.value: Hereditary combined deficiency of vitamin K-dependent clotting factors

definition.value: Combined vitamin K-dependent clotting factors deficiency (VKCFD) is a congenital bleeding disorder resulting from variably decreased levels of coagulation factors II, VII, IX and X, as well as natural anticoagulants protein C, protein S and protein Z.

OBSOLETE: Cystic malformation of the posterior fossa

definition.value: A rare group of neurodegenerative disorders with a prenatal onset characterized by hypoplasia and/or atrophy of the cerebellum and pons. Involvement of supratentorial structures is variable. Multiple forms have been described based on severity, age of onset and clinical presentation.
